# Medical Doctor and Interns SOP

  [bold]1.[/bold] Interns should focus on helping Medical Doctors and Surgeons in whatever they require, and tending to patients that require light care. If necessary, they can stand in for regular Medical Doctor duties;

  [bold]2.[/bold] Medical Doctors must place all corpses inside body bags and/or morgue trays. In addition, Medical Doctors must make sure that the Morgue does not contain reviveable corpses;

  [bold]3.[/bold] Medical Doctors are [bold]not[/bold] permitted to leave Medbay to perform recreational activities if there are unattended patients requiring treatment;

  [bold]4.[/bold] Medical Doctors are [bold]not[/bold] obliged to treat patients who are actively and intentionally harming themselves. 

  [bold]5.[/bold] Medical Doctors are to return any equipment of deceased crewmembers who have been moved to the morgue for permanent storage to their respective department.
